[1] BTV-8, 2007, update, week 48
Date: 4 Dec 2007
Source: AFSSA (French Sanitary Food Safety Agency) website
[translated, edited]
<http://www.afssa.fr/Documents/SANT-Fi-PtFCO.pdf>


BTV-8 outbreaks in Europe, 2007: update for week 48 (26 Nov - 2 Dec 2007)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
(Compiled by the unit for risk assessment in animal health and
nutrition, based upon the following sources: Afsca, Afssa (Lerpaz),
Cirad, Defra, DGAl, DG-SANCO ADNS, DVFA, OVF, Country presentations
to SCFCAH, ProMED.)

BTV-8 outbreaks confirmed in Europe since July 2007:
Germany - 18 896 outbreaks as of 23 Nov 2007 (not updated for week 48).
France - 11 894 outbreaks as of 26 Nov 2007, including 1294
confirmed during week 48.
Netherlands - 6158 outbreaks as of 5 Nov 2007 (not updated for week 48).
Belgium - 5994 outbreaks as of 3 Dec 2007, including 152 confirmed
during week 48.
Luxembourg - 1257 outbreaks as of 21 Nov 2007, including 43 confirmed
since 7 Nov 2007.
United Kingdom - 65 outbreaks as of 30 Nov 2007; no new outbreaks
confirmed during week 48.
Switzerland - 5 outbreaks as of 3 Dec 2007; no new outbreaks
confirmed during week 48.
Denmark - 1 outbreak as of 12 Nov 2007; no new outbreak confirmed
during week 48.
Czech Republic - 1 outbreak, newly infected during week 48.

In total, 44 271 outbreaks of BTV serotype 8 have been reported in
Europe since the beginning of July 2007. The highest disease
incidence was recorded in France during week 48.

--
Communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
Castleview Pedigree English Longhorns
Gut Laach
52385 Nideggen
